## 7. Collaboration, Communication, And Product Sense

As AI eats more of the low‑level execution work, the edge shifts toward **human coordination and product thinking**.

- **Communication**
  - Explaining trade‑offs and risks to non‑technical stakeholders.
  - Writing clear docs, ADRs (architecture decision records), and design proposals.
  - Giving and receiving high‑quality code reviews (even when some of the code was AI‑generated).

- **Product sense**
  - Understanding users well enough to say “this feature is not worth the complexity.”
  - Making decisions that balance ideal engineering with time‑to‑market.

- **Leadership without title**
  - Guiding less experienced teammates on how to work with AI effectively.
  - Setting quality bars: “What does ‘good enough’ look like in this context?”

AI does not attend planning meetings. It does not align stakeholders. It does not say “no” to bad ideas. You do.

